# Documentation & contributor hub

## Default posture

Treat **up-to-date documentation as continuous work**, not an afterthought. When you finish a **milestone**, **feature**, or **merge-worthy change**, documentation should move in the same effort (same PR or immediate follow-up), not later.

## What to update (match the change)

| Change type | Typical updates |
|-------------|-----------------|
| User-visible behavior, structure, or workflows | `README.md`, relevant `docs/*.md`, `docs/DOC_MAP.md` if behaviors traceability shifts, `docs/REPOSITORY_MANIFEST.md` for new/renamed policy paths |
| Release or notable batch of work | `CHANGELOG.md` **Unreleased** section |
| Agent or Cursor expectations | `AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/rules/` together with policy docs |
| Maintainer status, branches, next actions | `.planning/STATE.md` |

## Contributor hub (`dashboard/`)

**Methodical upkeep:** Follow **[docs/DEV_DASHBOARD.md](../../docs/DEV_DASHBOARD.md)** (“Contributor hub maintenance playbook”) so counts, generated sections, and STATE/Canvas stay aligned; CI runs **`scripts/verify_dashboard_consistency.py`** on PRs.

The HTML **contributor hub** is [`dashboard/index.html`](../../dashboard/index.html). It is the guided entry for new contributors: from the repo root run `python -m http.server 8765`, then open that file in the browser (local URL `http://localhost:8765/dashboard/`). It may load **Google Fonts** and **`marked`** from CDNs when online; **`dashboard/README.md`** describes privacy/offline behavior.

**Domain landing pages (`dashboard/domains/`)** must stay aligned with the YAML catalog: bridge counts come from each bridge’s **`fields`** list matched to `unknowns-catalog/<domain>/` (see **`scripts/domain_matching.py`**). After batches of **bridges / unknowns / hypotheses**, regenerate pages — **`python scripts/generate_domain_pages.py`** (runs in **`build-graph.yml`** when catalog paths change). CI runs **`python scripts/verify_domain_pages.py`** (minimum bridge visibility checks). Ship regenerated HTML with the same PR as the catalog change when feasible.

**Breakthrough gaps (`breakthrough-gaps/*.yaml`)** drive the hub “Breakthrough Gaps” grid via **`scripts/render_breakthrough_gaps_hub.py --apply`** (also runs from **`build-graph.yml`** when gap YAML changes). Steward expectations: **`docs/BREAKTHROUGH_GAPS.md`**.

