- If **onboarding paths**, **section order**, **key links**, or **major hub UX** (layout, theme, nav) change, update **`dashboard/index.html`** and, when maintainers need the story, **`dashboard/README.md`** / **`docs/DEV_DASHBOARD.md`**.
- If **unknown/hypothesis schemas** or **seed YAML examples** change the steps a newcomer follows, update **`docs/HAPPY_PATH_FIRST_RECORDS.md`** (Stream A) in the same change.
- After editing **`.planning/STATE.md`**, refresh the Cursor Canvas snapshot in `canvases/Progress.canvas.tsx` when that file exists; run **`python scripts/sync-dashboard-from-state.py`** (Canvas embeds constants; the HTML hub loads STATE live only over HTTP).
- Before considering work **done**, sanity-check the hub: start **`python -m http.server 8765`** from the repo root, open **[`dashboard/index.html`](../../dashboard/index.html)** at **`http://localhost:8765/dashboard/`**, confirm sections load, theme/nav if you touched them, and links are not broken for the paths you changed.

## MkDocs

If **`docs/`** or **`mkdocs.yml`** changed, run **`mkdocs build --strict`** and fix warnings before merge.

## Scope

This rule governs **meta** documentation and navigation. It does not relax scientific rigor from `science-discovery-core.mdc`: no new scientific claims in checklist or hub text without following methodology and evidence docs.
